events.name: GDG Cloud Atlanta 2019 Kickoff Meetup!!

venue.name: Google Atlanta HQ
venue.address_1: Google Atlanta  - 10 10th Street NE #600 Atlanta, GA 30309

events.description:
Details:

Come join us at the Google Atlanta office on January 23rd to kick off our Atlanta GDG chapter for Google Cloud! Please register here so we can get you in the building: http://bit.ly/GDGATL_form .

The theme for the night will be building products/solutions utilizing Google Cloud’s ML/AI components.
- We’ll demo how AutoML Vision can be used to automatically build/train an ML model used to detect skin disease.
- We’ll follow that with presentations from both Farmwave and Engage Talent on how they’ve integrated Google AI/ML into their solutions.
- To round out the night, we’ll have a panel discussion with Craig Ganssle (CEO, Farmwave), Robby Gulri (CMO of Engage Talent), and Google ML experts.

We’ll provide food and drinks.

Look forward to seeing you there!

Agenda
6:00 - 6:30 PM Networking

6:30 - 6:40 PM Introductions/Opening Remarks - Craig/Mike

6:40 - 7:00 PM AutoML Vision (Slides + Demo) - Mike

7:00 - 7:15 PM Farmwave Presentation - Craig Ganssle

7:15 - 7:30 PM Engage Presentation - Robby Gulri

7:30 - 8:30 PM Panel Discussion - Craig Ganssle, Robby Gulri, Sanjay Agravat, TBD

8:30 - 9:00 PM Closing Remarks/Networking
events.how_to_find_us: Parking is available in the attached parking deck off of West Peachtree for a fee.  Marta is also an option as the office is directly across from the Midtown station.  Once in the building, take the elevators to the 6th floor.

events.name: Chick-fil-A: Milking the Most Out of Thousands of Kubernetes Clusters
events.description:
***THIS IS S JOINT EVENT WITH THE GCP ANALYTICS ATLANTA GROUP***

Join us and the GCP Analytics Atlanta Meetup Group for a combined event.
https://gcpmeetup.eventzilla.net/web/event?eventid=2138719589

Chick-fil-A is in the midst of rolling out a Kubernetes cluster at the edge in each of their restaurants, as well as implementing it to back the API’s that drive their Chick-fil-A One mobile app. During this talk, Caleb will focus on the Edge/IoT platform from a design and scale perspective and why Kubernetes is taking the tech world by storm. Come ready to ask questions as we hope to have a lively Q+A discussion.

Biography:
Caleb Hurd, Chick-fil-A
Caleb Hurd is a Site Reliability Engineer at Chick-fil-A. His passion is enabling small development teams to deliver their software reliably and rapidly to customers by empowering them with the tools and pipelines to do so.

Details
Join us for our first GCP Analytics Atlanta Meetup. The agenda and presentation details can be found below. We look forward to talking GCP with you!

6:00 pm - 6:30 pm: Refreshments and Networking
6:30 pm - 7:15 pm: Introduction and Caleb Hurd, Presentation
7:15 pm - 8:00 pm: Additional Q&A & Networking

events.name: The Data Visualization Iceberg: Beneath the Surface with Data Studio and Looker
events.description:
Our August Meetup event is sponsored by Equifax. Join us and the GCP Analytics Atlanta Meetup Group at the Equifax Office at One Atlantic Center in Midtown for our first meetup together as one GCP Group. The agenda and presentation details can be found below. We look forward to talking GCP with you!

Abstract:

As much as 90 percent of the iceberg is below the surface of the ocean. Analytics platforms are similar: data visualizations are typically what the user sees, but much of the complexity of end-to-end data delivery is hidden beneath the surface.

In this presentation, we’ll dive into the ocean with both Google Data Studio and Looker to see how complete analytics solutions are built using each platform. We’ll consider the role of data engineering, data prep, and data modeling in producing the catalog we source for data visualizations, and we’ll also explore how these products can be used to power analytics in external applications.

Speaker:

Stewart Bryson, CEO & Founder @Red Pill Analytics
Stewart Bryson is the founder and CEO of Red Pill Analytics, and has been designing and implementing data and analytics systems since 1996. He is an internationally recognized writer and speaker, and an Oracle ACE Director, Oracle’s highest tier of community advocacy.

Agenda:
Food and Beverages Provide by Equifax

6:00 - 6:30 PM | Networking
6:30 - 6:45 PM | Announcements/Introductions
6:45 - 7:15 PM | CTO of Equifax to Discuss their current Transformation to GCP
7:15 - 8:00 PM | The Data Visualization Iceberg - Stewart Bryson
8:00 - 8:30 PM | Q&A/Networking

Parking Notes and Instructions:

Parking available in the One Atlantic Center Parking Garage. Once parked, take the elevator to level C. Follow the tunnel through the double glass doors and up the escalator. Proceed to the lobby reception desk and provide your name. Inform the reception desk you are attending a Google Cloud Meet up at Equifax on the 20th floor. You will then be provided with access to the set of elevators 18-29. Take the elevator to the 20th floor to the Equifax reception desk. Go through the double doors to the Equifax reception desk. Please have a photo ID ready for the reception desk.

events.name: Cloud Developer Day
events.description:
In lieu of planning a separate Meetup event for November, we'd like to invite GDG Cloud members to the upcoming Cloud Developer Day.

On November 14th Equifax and Google Cloud are teaming up to host Cloud Developer Day at the Computer Museum of America. Together, both companies have been building out the future of enterprise technology and we’re excited to share the learnings and insights with the local community. Learn how Google Cloud technologies are powering Equifax’s journey into a technology company and how the people are embracing the culture shift. Here’s more about what to expect:

- Interact with technology experts and senior executives from Google Cloud, Equifax, and EPAM
- Why the partnership between Equifax and Google Cloud is essential to enterprise transformation
- A showcase of the latest Equifax developer projects on Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
- See why Equifax is a great place to build out technology
- Best practices for shifting from legacy to cloud-native
- Hands-on, competitive learning opportunities (prizes for the winners)
- Meet our partner and official event sponsor, EPAM
- Peer-to-peer networking
- A look ahead to future technologies and developments
- Insights as to how enterprises are making the most of Cloud technology

Space is limited, so register now to reserve your spot.

PLEASE REGISTER AT THE EVENT LINK: http://bit.ly/gdgcloudatlnov

events.name: Which Whiskey: Predicting Whiskey Preferences with GCP & G Suite

venue.name: CRIB
venue.address_2: Suite 130 (Ground Floor behind Minnie Olivia Pizzeria)

events.description:
Note: This is a combined event with The Big Data ATL Meetup Group
Please RSVP using https://www.eventbrite.com/e/which-whiskey-predicting-whiskey-preferences-with-gcp-g-suite-tickets-90854760033 to confirm your registration for this event

What happens when one guy's passion for whiskey and the cloud collide? An ML model that will predict which whiskies he'll enjoy, of course! In this talk, Phil will outline how he created a simple but powerful application using G Suite and Google Cloud to predict his whiskey preferences, and how to apply those lessons learned to an enterprise cloud setting.

Agenda:
6:30 - 7:00 PM Networking, Food and Beverages
7:00 - 7:45 PM Which Whiskey
7:45 - 8:00 PM Q&A

Presenter: Phil Goerdt, Cloud Consultant with Google Cloud's Professional Services team
He helps organizations move to and make the most of their Google Cloud Platform implementations. He's been in consulting for over 10 years and has been working with data for even longer. When he isn't thinking about data, tech or business, you can find him on the hunt for new foods try, whiskies to sample and books read. He lives in Chicago.

events.name: Ensuring Business Continuity in Your Organization with the Google SRE team
events.description:
Google is running a webinar series every Thursday at 1:00pm EST for their tech community. They will discuss how you can leverage specific technology to address your most pressing issues. The GDG Cloud Atlanta has been invited to attend for free.

I am posting this first one for April 30th and if there is a high interest, I'll post the invites to the others as a repeat event.

Thursday, April 30, 2020 Event:

The Google Site Reliability Engineering team (known as the SRE team) knows a thing or two about keeping the light on for a global infrastructure billions of users depend on. Come learn about how they do it for Google and learn about the best practices they recommend for other organizations to adopt.

Register here: https://events.withgoogle.com/tech-talk-how-to-apply-best-practices-for-business-continuity-google-sre-practice-a-talk-on-sy/registrations/new/

Once you register you should be given the link to attend.

events.name: [Google Tech Talk] - Okay Kelsey, Tell me how!
events.description:
Google Webinar Series

If you could get 15 minutes with Kelsey Hightower, what would you ask? Well you’re in luck! This week Kelsey will share bright ideas for staying afloat and outpacing your competition. Kelsey will answer your questions, and share how Kubernetes increases business agility and allows you to innovate and respond to changes in the market faster.
